Actuator = An actuator is an electronic device controlled 
			by a motor that moves the hard drive head arm.

Access arm = Alternatively referred to as read/write head 
			arm, head arm, or actuator arm, the access 
			arm is in every mechanical hard drive.

Head = A read/write head or RW head is a device found on 
		the arm of a hard drive that is used to read and
		write data from the hard drive's disk platter.' 

Spindle =  In the case of a hard drive, as seen in the 
			picture below, the spindle is what holds a
			hard drives platters in place.

Platter = One or more aluminum, glass, or ceramic disk
			that is coated in a magnetic media and is 
			located within a hard drive to permanently
			store all your computer's data.' 

Disk controller = Printed circuitry that contains the 
					necessary instructions for disk
					drives. 